      Mission Text Block   To enable excellence through information technology        VISION         Vision Text block   To be a trusted strategic partner for innovative and transformative information technology solutions        VALUES         Values text block     Values Text block   Collaboration  We work to develop, expand and enhance partnerships across the university and its community while promoting collaboration and shared knowledge.  Excellence We strive for the best customer service, are proactive in our planning and responsive when issues arise.     Empty as well   Innovation  We utilize our talents to foster innovative and creative solutions.  Integrity We act responsibly, ethically, and without bias, basing our decisions on facts and data. We recognize our role as public employees and work sustainably and with stewardship.     column 3   People We encourage professional and personal growth and respect the work/life balance of our employees. We show each other respect and listen to each other’s thoughts and ideas.  Transparency We openly communicate internally and with the university community to foster accountability.           PRINCIPLES         Principes text block   As an organization, we agree to the following principles to guide our work.       bullet points     bullet points    Be a good steward of resources  Be a people-first place to work      bullet points two electric bugaloo    Be intentional in our partnerships  Commit to continuous improvement and learning      column 3    Deliver customer-centered service  Embrace an innovative culture of ideas and solutions            STRATEGIC GOALS         intro text   The following organizational goals have short term and long term activities with detailed action plans and projects.       Strategic Goals Text block     Strategic goals text block    Achieve fiscal sustainability  Align our service portfolio to meet the needs of the university  Balance resources to innovate while maintaining service excellence      bullet points    Enhance University’s information security and privacy posture to reduce cyber risks  Improve customer satisfaction  Improve staff recruitment, retention, and development  Improve the reputation of the department throughout the university      bullets three    Incubate innovative ideas from across the university  Make data-driven decisions  Mature the implementation of service management practices  Strengthen partnerships for ongoing and future university needs                 ACCC Projects & Strategic Goals          About    Back to main content           Identity    Leadership    Policies    Reports    Jobs                   UIC Logo         Academic  Computing  And  Communications  Center           Quick Links    Services    Support    Service Status    News    Forms    About      Support Locations    Academic Multimedia Lab    ARC Helpdesk    C-Stop BSB    C-Stop LHS    Daley Library Helpdesk    LTS Support Office        Footer Menu    HIPAA    IAM Password Manager    Information Security    IT Governance    Jobs    Policies    Research (ACER)    Sign Up for UIC Emergency Alerts    ACCC Drupal Site         Contact   To report a service outage please call (312) 413-0003 option 2  consult@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 